2019-12-19 01:31:44	null4bl3	hi guys.. for pytest.. do i really need to have the 'test_*' file in the same directory as my coded project? it feels wrong for big projects
2019-12-19 01:32:32	<--	F2Knight (~textual@50-39-203-208.bvtn.or.frontiernet.net) has quit (Remote host closed the connection)
2019-12-19 01:32:59	-->	Soni (~quassel@unaffiliated/soniex2) has joined #python
2019-12-19 01:33:11	cdunklau	null4bl3: nope
2019-12-19 01:33:21	altendky	null4bl3: there are lots of options.  i have a mypkg.tests packages with sub packages and modules.  other people have a tests/ directory in the root of their project.  there are more options as well
2019-12-19 01:33:43	cdunklau	you can put it anywhere, really. i tend to have a tests package inside my project's package
2019-12-19 01:33:58	-->	rdejoux (~rdejoux@proxy-109-190-254-4.ovh.net) has joined #python
2019-12-19 01:33:59	cdunklau	sometimes i separate tests and source
