2019-12-19 01:35:54	cdunklau	null4bl3: when you e.g. `import pathlib`, you're importing the stdlib module from somewhere totally different (unless you've made a terrible mistake)
2019-12-19 01:36:00	altendky	null4bl3: i say that things you import should be installed.  so your project you are testing should be installed.  my tests usually have a utility file etc they use by importing so it should be installed.  i'd rather keep it with my tests and i don't want a second package (of just tests) to install so i put it all in my main package.
